other_tests.findings: There is a trace right pleural effusion with mild to moderate bilateral dependent atelectasis. The gallbladder is distended, with a thickened wall and extensive pericholecystic fat stranding. There is a hyperdense gallstone in the gallbladder fundus measuring 5 mm. The pancreas, spleen, urinary system, reproductive organs, and lymph nodes appear normal. There is extensive atherosclerotic disease and chronic occlusion of the proximal SMA with reconstitution shortly distally.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Grade 1 anterolisthesis of L4 and L5 is unchanged. Moderate multilevel degenerative changes of the lumbar spine are similar to the prior study.
